mmetry breaking\">spontaneous broken symmetry<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Subatomic\" title=\"Subatomic\" class=\"mw-redirect\">subatomic<\/a> physics, related at first to the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Strong_interaction\" title=\"Strong interaction\">strong interaction<\/a>'s <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Chiral_symmetry\" title=\"Chiral symmetry\">chiral symmetry<\/a> and later to the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Electroweak_interaction\" title=\"Electroweak interaction\">electroweak interaction<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Higgs_mechanism\" title=\"Higgs mechanism\">Higgs mechanism<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nobel_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Yoichiro_Nambu#cite_note-Nobel-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> The other half share was split equally between <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Makoto_Kobayashi_(physicist)\" title=\"Makoto Kobayashi (physicist)\">Makoto Kobayashi<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Toshihide_Maskawa\" title=\"Toshihide Maskawa\">Toshihide Maskawa<\/a> \"for the discovery of the origin of the broken symmetry which predicts the existence of at least three families of quarks in nature.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Yoichiro_Nambu#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Yoichiro Nambu","place_of_birth":"Tokyo, Japan","place_of_death":null,"text":"Yoichiro Nambu , Physics, 2008","year":2008.0}